Schema keeps the generated columns:
a	Nullable(Int64)					
b	Nullable(Int64)					
c	Nullable(Int64)					
Insert without a column list, and an explicit base-column list, both target only the base columns; SQLite computes the generated columns:
a	b	c
1	2	2
2	3	4
Generated columns are MATERIALIZED, so SELECT * returns only the base columns:
a
1
2
Explicitly writing into a generated column is rejected:
Cannot insert column b, because it is MATERIALIZED column
The rejected insert wrote nothing:
a	b	c
1	2	2
2	3	4
